  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2020-03-09",
    "date": "2021-08-20T01:26:01Z",
    "text": "USA FREEDOM Reauthorization Act of 2020\n\nThis bill modifies provisions related to foreign intelligence surveillance. Among other things, the bill (1) repeals authorities providing for ongoing access to call detail records; (2) requires the Office of the Director of National Intelligence to decide whether to declassify a significant Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Court decision within 180 days of the decision; and (3) requires government officers to disclose all relevant information, including any exculpatory information, when applying for a court order under certain foreign surveillance authorities."
